[1] dotplot.array*   dotplot.default* dotplot.formula* dotplot.matrix*  dotplot.numeric*

dotplot(VADeaths, groups = FALSE)

dotplot(VADeaths,
  groups = FALSE,
  layout = c(1, 4), aspect = 0.7,
  origin = 0, type = c("p", "h"),
  main = "Death Rates in Virginia - 1940",
  xlab = "Rate (per 1000)"
)

dotplot(VADeaths,
  type = "o",
  auto.key = list(lines = TRUE, space = "right"),
  main = "Death Rates in Virginia - 1940",
  xlab = "Rate (per 1000)"
)

4.2 Bar chart

barchart(VADeaths,
  groups = FALSE,
  layout = c(1, 4),
  aspect = 0.7,
  reference = FALSE,
  main = "Death Rates in Virginia - 1940",
  xlab = "Rate (per 1000)"
)

data(postdoc, package = "latticeExtra")
class(postdoc)
[1] "table"
barchart(prop.table(postdoc, margin = 1),
  xlab = "Proposrtion",
  auto.key = list(adj = 1)
)

dotplot(prop.table(postdoc, margin = 1),
  groups = FALSE,
  xlab = "Propostion",
  par.strip.text = list(abbreviate = TRUE, minlength = 10)
)

dotplot(prop.table(postdoc, margin = 1),
  groups = FALSE,
  index.cond = function(x, y) median(x),
  layout = c(1, 5), aspect = 0.6,
  xlab = "Proportion",
  scales = list(y = list(relation = "free", rot = 0)),
  prepanel = function(x, y) {
    list(ylim = levels(reorder(y, x)))
  },
  panel = function(x, y, ...) {
    panel.dotplot(x, reorder(y, x), ...)
  }
)

data(Chem97, package = "mlmRev")
gcsescore.tab <- xtabs(~ gcsescore + gender, Chem97)
head(gcsescore.tab)
         gender
gcsescore M F
    0     1 0
    1     2 0
    1.5   0 1
    2     1 0
    2.083 1 0
    2.428 1 1
gcsescore.df <- as.data.frame(gcsescore.tab)
gcsescore.df
gcsescore.df$gcsescore <- as.numeric(as.character(gcsescore.df$gcsescore))
xyplot(Freq ~ gcsescore | gender,
  data = gcsescore.df,
  type = "h",
  layout = c(1, 2),
  xlab = "Average GCSE Score"
)

score.tab <- xtabs(~ score + gender, Chem97)
score.df <- as.data.frame(score.tab)
barchart(Freq ~ score | gender, score.df, origin = 0)

barchart(Freq ~ score,
  data = score.df,
  groups = gender,
  auto.key = TRUE,
  origin = 0
)
